  "prompt": "Does IIM Indore select 1 year dropouts for IPM?",
  "response": "The Integrated Program in Management (IPM) at IIM Indore is a unique five-year program that combines undergraduate and postgraduate studies. Admission criteria for IPM primarily include academic performance, aptitude test scores, and personal interviews.\n\nAs for applicants who have taken a one-year dropout, IIM Indore does not specifically disqualify candidates with a gap year. However, they generally look for consistency and strong academic performance throughout a student's educational journey. Applicants with a gap year are encouraged to provide valid reasons for the dropout and should be prepared to discuss how they utilized that time effectively, whether through relevant work experience, additional studies, or productive activities that contributed to their personal growth.\n\nUltimately, each application is considered on a case-by-case basis, and demonstrating resilience, a clear purpose, and continuous self-improvement can positively impact the assessment of candidates with unconventional academic histories.",
